[[Image:Teresa Teng MTHK.jpg|thumb|The wax figure of Teresa Teng at [[Madame Tussauds Hong Kong]]]]
 
Teng died from a severe [[asthma]] attack while on holiday in [[Chiang Mai]], [[Thailand]] at the age of 42 (43 by [[East Asian age reckoning|Chinese reckoning]]) on May 8, 1995. She was an asthmatic throughout her adult life. Teng was given [[state funeral|state honors]] at her funeral in Taiwan, with the [[flag of the Republic of China]] draped over her casket and then president [[Lee Teng-hui]] in attendance among thousands in mourning.
